# **Important Rule: `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` Values Bake at Build Time**

Any value beginning with:

```
NEXT_PUBLIC_
```

is compiled into the client bundle during:

```shell
next build
```

Changing one later requires a **full rebuild and redeploy**, not just a restart. [\[phases-checklist | Word\]](https://mangupublishinghouse-my.sharepoint.com/personal/ravigopal_mangupublishinghouse_onmicrosoft_com/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc=%7B077D3EA2-BF7F-4980-B2CD-E8690B300088%7D&file=phases-checklist.docx&action=default&mobileredirect=true)

This matters especially for:

```
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL
```

If these are wrong during build, production may call localhost, redirect incorrectly, or use stale public config. [\[phases-checklist | Word\]](https://mangupublishinghouse-my.sharepoint.com/personal/ravigopal_mangupublishinghouse_onmicrosoft_com/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc=%7B077D3EA2-BF7F-4980-B2CD-E8690B300088%7D&file=phases-checklist.docx&action=default&mobileredirect=true)

