## **A4.3 — PKCE Code-Verifier Gotcha**

This is a common failure mode.

Supabase JS may use PKCE. That means the browser used to register stores a code verifier, and the confirmation link must be opened in the **same browser/device**.

Test:

Register in desktop Chrome  
Open the confirmation email link in the same Chrome profile

If this works but cross-device fails, PKCE verifier mismatch is the issue.

Common log signatures:

both auth code and code verifier should be non-empty  
invalid flow state  
\`\`

Potential fixes:

accept same-browser limitation  
switch template to token\_hash \+ verifyOtp()  
use an implicit-flow-compatible approach

[\[phases-checklist | Word\]](https://mangupublishinghouse-my.sharepoint.com/personal/ravigopal_mangupublishinghouse_onmicrosoft_com/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc=%7B077D3EA2-BF7F-4980-B2CD-E8690B300088%7D&file=phases-checklist.docx&action=default&mobileredirect=true)

## **A4.4 — Middleware Interference**

Confirm:

/callback is not protected by middleware  
/callback is not redirected away before exchange  
rate limiter is not catching /callback during repeated tests

