# **8.1 — Fix Broken CI Workflows**

## **Goal**

Fix GitHub Actions workflows that silently skip deploy jobs because they use unsupported `secrets.*` references inside job-level `if:` conditions. [\[phases-checklist | Word\]](https://mangupublishinghouse-my.sharepoint.com/personal/ravigopal_mangupublishinghouse_onmicrosoft_com/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc=%7B077D3EA2-BF7F-4980-B2CD-E8690B300088%7D&file=phases-checklist.docx&action=default&mobileredirect=true)

## **Root Cause**

The checklist identifies this pattern as broken:

if: secrets.SOME\_SECRET \!= ''

at the **job level**.

GitHub Actions does not support using `secrets.*` directly in job-level `if:` in the intended way, causing deploy jobs to silently skip. [\[phases-checklist | Word\]](https://mangupublishinghouse-my.sharepoint.com/personal/ravigopal_mangupublishinghouse_onmicrosoft_com/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc=%7B077D3EA2-BF7F-4980-B2CD-E8690B300088%7D&file=phases-checklist.docx&action=default&mobileredirect=true)

---

## **Files to Inspect**

.github/workflows/ci.yml  
.github/workflows/deploy.yml  
---

## **8.1.a — Find Invalid Secret-Based Conditions**

Run:

grep \-n "if:.\*secrets." .github/workflows/ci.yml .github/workflows/deploy.yml

Record every occurrence.

---

## **8.1.b — Replace Invalid Conditions**

Replace job-level `secrets.*` checks with one of these safer patterns:

### **Option A — Repo / org variable gate**

Example:

if: vars.DEPLOY\_ENABLED \== 'true'  
\`\`

### **Option B — Explicit check-secrets step**

Use a previous job or step that checks for required inputs and writes a safe output, then gate later jobs on that output.

Example concept:

needs.check-secrets.outputs.ready \== 'true'

The checklist allows either a repo/org variable gate or an upstream check step that exposes a job output. [\[phases-checklist | Word\]](https://mangupublishinghouse-my.sharepoint.com/personal/ravigopal_mangupublishinghouse_onmicrosoft_com/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc=%7B077D3EA2-BF7F-4980-B2CD-E8690B300088%7D&file=phases-checklist.docx&action=default&mobileredirect=true)

---

## **8.1.c — Fix Secret Handling in `deploy.yml`**

In addition to fixing `if:` conditions, update deployment secret handling so Cloud Run uses **Secret Manager references**, not plain environment variable values. [\[phases-checklist | Word\]](https://mangupublishinghouse-my.sharepoint.com/personal/ravigopal_mangupublishinghouse_onmicrosoft_com/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc=%7B077D3EA2-BF7F-4980-B2CD-E8690B300088%7D&file=phases-checklist.docx&action=default&mobileredirect=true)

Expected direction:

Cloud Run env should reference Secret Manager secrets.  
Do not inject secrets as plain runtime env vars.

This should match the same model used by `cloudbuild.yaml`. [\[phases-checklist | Word\]](https://mangupublishinghouse-my.sharepoint.com/personal/ravigopal_mangupublishinghouse_onmicrosoft_com/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc=%7B077D3EA2-BF7F-4980-B2CD-E8690B300088%7D&file=phases-checklist.docx&action=default&mobileredirect=true)

---

