## **Phase 11 — Known-Issues Lookup Table**

**Purpose:** Phase 11 is an always-on diagnostic reference. Before treating any failure as novel, agents must check this table first, match the symptom if possible, apply the documented resolution, verify the fix, and preserve recurrence guards. This prevents wasting time re-diagnosing already-known issues. [\[phases-checklist | Word\]](https://mangupublishinghouse-my.sharepoint.com/personal/ravigopal_mangupublishinghouse_onmicrosoft_com/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc=%7B077D3EA2-BF7F-4980-B2CD-E8690B300088%7D&file=phases-checklist.docx&action=default&mobileredirect=true)

---

# **Phase 11 Operating Rule**

Before escalating or troubleshooting from scratch:

```
1. Identify the symptom.
2. Search the Phase 11 known-issues table.
3. If a row matches, apply the listed resolution.
4. Run the “verify fix worked” check.
5. Confirm the recurrence guard is in place.
6. Only escalate if no match exists or the known fix fails.
```

This directly supports the global **Known-Issue Rule** from Phase 0\. [\[phases-checklist | Word\]](https://mangupublishinghouse-my.sharepoint.com/personal/ravigopal_mangupublishinghouse_onmicrosoft_com/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc=%7B077D3EA2-BF7F-4980-B2CD-E8690B300088%7D&file=phases-checklist.docx&action=default&mobileredirect=true)

